==English==

===Etymology===
from [[opthamology]]: Greek ''[[οφθαλμός]]'' (''opthalmos'') "eye" + ''[[-λογία]]'' (''-logia'') "the study of" (from [[λόγος]] "logos")

===Noun===
'''ophthalmologist'''
#A medical [[doctor]] specializing in the [[eye]]: deficiencies of [[vision]] requiring correction, and [[disease]]s.  Compare [[optometrist]].